## Proposed changes

Issue Number: close #20868

FloatLiteral uses == to compare floating-point number, which will encounter loss of percision, and will get unexpected result

```java
private void init(Double value) {
        this.value = value.doubleValue();
        // Figure out if this will fit in a FLOAT without losing precision.
        float fvalue;
        fvalue = value.floatValue();
        if (fvalue == this.value) {
            // here uses == to compare floating-point number, which will encounter loss of percision, and will get unexpected result
            type = Type.FLOAT;
        } else {
            type = Type.DOUBLE;
        }
    }
```

